race.comment: COSMIC CRUSADER (5) will line up here after failing to gain a start in the Railway last week. He had no luck there in the Peters off a moderate tempo where he was boxed in until the dying stages. Suspect they won't leave anything up to luck this time, he'll roll forward and get back to winning ways. ASPHALT (10) made it six wins in a row last start with a gutsy performance over the mile here just last week, beating a handy field. Back to 1400m today looks a good move and he's sure to be handy from the draw. Can continue his winning run without surprising. YONGA LASS (6) disappointed in the Lee Steere but was great fresh at Kalgoorlie. Pike now hops back aboard and her third-up record is solid. Ready to peak now and can put her best foot forward. AZTEC RULER (2) wasn't far away in the Peters off a slow tempo where he was caught wide. Can feature again. Hoping we get a strong tempo so we can see where ZIPAWAY (1) is at enroute to the Perth Cup.
